en_9872827_0	Can you fathom the pain that a mother feels when she loses her child.
en_9872827_1	Can you imagine the emotions that run amok when a father loses sight of his child….
en_9872827_2	This is the story of a daughter and a son who lost the warmth of their loving parents, till today… The day, December 26,2004.
en_9872827_3	A fateful day which left a permanent scar on the lives of many Sri Lankans.
en_9872827_4	A day that ended, leaving thousands lifeless, missing and bringing tears to all Sri Lankans alike.
en_9872827_5	Little Sherifa was only just three-years-old when the deadly waves separated her from the clutches of her dear father….
en_9872827_6	Her father said “We went to the Hambantota and Kataragama police stations when we were looking for her.”
en_9872827_7	Since then, all attempts made by Sherifa’s parents to locate their little girl, proved futile.
en_9872827_8	In a strange twist of fate, a photograph of a girl lost in the tsunami was being circulated on the internet.
en_9872827_9	The image caught the attention of one of Sherifa’s relatives.
en_9872827_10	Hope was restored when this relative brought the photograph to the attention Sherifa’s parents, after noticing that the girl bore a stark resemblance to Sherifa.
en_9872827_11	Filled with hope, the family headed to Kalmunai in search of the girl in the photograph.
en_9872827_12	During their meeting, the parents identified their daughter from her bodily marks and her familiar features.
en_9872827_13	However, the parents had to seek the help of courts to obtain the legal rights for their daughter.
en_9872827_14	Finally the lucky day dawned – on Wednesday, August 3, as it was proven before courts that this little girls is infact their daughter, Sherifa.
en_9872827_15	Fort police managed unite ten month old Rilvan who went missing two days ago, on August 2,  with his mother.
en_9872827_16	Living at the Fort Railway Station, the mother took her dear son to the Galle Face Green on Tuesday.
en_9872827_17	During their time there, the child was kidnapped when she went to the toilet.
en_9872827_18	However even before the lapse of a day the police, following the information given by the mother, managed to arrest the suspect who kidnapped the child in Chilaw.
en_9872827_19	The suspect, a 34-year-old resident of Kirulapone, is in remand custody after being produced before courts.
